<HEADER>
A2234 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBC-BAYLOR-STALLINGS-     12-10 0543
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-BAYLOR-STALLINGS-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By TERRY BLOUNT  
 c. 1998, Houston Chronicle  
WACO _ Former Alabama coach Gene Stallings has been offered the job
of replacing Dave Roberts as Baylor's head football coach, sources
said Wednesday.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Also, Dallas Highland Park coach Scott Smith has been contacted
about taking the position of defensive coordinator, sources
confirmed.
</P>
<P>
   Stallings, who won the 1992 national championship at Alabama,
wants some time to consider the offer and how he would handle a
prior commitment to the USA World Cup team, which is scheduled to
play in Europe next summer.
</P>
<P>
   Baylor athletic director Tom Stanton decided to reassign Roberts
on Sunday, two weeks after Roberts and the Bears had completed
their second consecutive 2-9 season. Rumors concerning Stallings,
63, surfaced the same day.
</P>
<P>
   Smith, 40, is a former player and assistant coach at Baylor.
</P>
<P>
   When asked if an announcement is coming soon, Smith said, ``I
don't know how much I can say. All I can say is what I've said
before: I love Baylor University, and I certainly would be
interested in Baylor.''
</P>
<P>
   Dr. John Connally, the Highland Park athletic director, said it
was ``a little premature right now'' to say Smith was leaving the
school.
</P>
<P>
   Stallings, who has a ranch in Paris, Texas, was in Jacksonville,
Fla., Monday and Tuesday on a book tour but flew to Dallas on
Wednesday and stayed at the home of one of his daughters. Sources
said Stanton was in Dallas on Wednesday on business.
</P>
<P>
   Stallings is scheduled to be at a news conference this morning
in Granbury to announce the site of the USA team's training camp
for the first World Cup of American Football, which will be played
in Italy in July. Stallings was selected by the American Football
Coaches Association to coach the team of college all-stars.
</P>
<P>
   But NCAA rules will not permit an active coach to participate in
the World Cup, so Stallings likely would have to resign his
position as coach of the USA team if he took the job at Baylor.
</P>
<P>
   Todd Bell, the director of media relations for the AFCA, said
Wednesday night he still expected Stallings to be at the news
conference, and the announcement in Granbury would take place
whether or not Stallings was present.
</P>
<P>
   ``As of now, he is still the coach of the team,'' Bell said.
</P>
<P>
   Baylor officials hope to make an announcement on a new coach as
soon as possible, because each day without a head coach essentially
is a lost day in the recruiting process.
</P>
<P>
   But sources said Stanton still plans to interview Southern
Mississippi coach Jeff Bower, who is believed to be Baylor's second
choice if Stallings turns down the school's offer.
</P>
<P>
   The other factor in this equation is Smith, who is a highly
respected high school coach who could be groomed to take over the
Baylor program under a veteran tutor like Stallings.
</P>
<P>
   Smith played quarterback and defensive back at Baylor from
1977-81 under Grant Teaff before coaching defensive backs for Teaff
for three seasons. Sources said Teaff has highly recommended Smith
to Baylor officials.
</P>
<P>
   If Stallings takes the job, he will be working with his
son-in-law, Keith Gunn, who is an administrative assistant coach at
Baylor.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
