   &UR; INTERNATIONAL _ (Moved in ``i'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   NKOREA-FOOD (Beijing) _ More than five years of severe food
shortages and a near-total breakdown in the public health system
have led to devastating malnutrition in North Korea and probably
left an entire generation of children physically and mentally
impaired, a new study by international aid groups has found. By
Elisabeth Rosenthal.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: A map and a graphic have been sent to NYT graphics
clients.)
