<P>
   STEEL-COMPETE (BETHLEHEM, Pa.) _ With appearances before
Congress, arm-twisting of the Clinton administration, a
sophisticated publicity campaign and a barrage of lawsuits, leaders
of the domestic steel industry are fighting to protect it from the
low prices and cutthroat competition brought on by the global
financial crisis and a flood of imports from Asia, Latin America
and Russia. By Leslie Wayne.
</P>
