   YIELD-CURVE-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ With the yield on the
30-year bond below 5 percent again, investors seem to be signaling
that they are even happier about the outlook for inflation than
they were. But, at the same time, they may be worried anew that the
Federal Reserve has not done enough to protect the U.S. economy
from being tripped up by the global financial crisis. By Jonathan
Fuerbringer.
