A2552 &Cx1f; tad-z
u i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-MIDEAST-ISSUES     12-10 0296
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MIDEAST-ISSUES </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    CLINTON, SEEKING MIDEAST PEACE, FACES SHORT-TERM DEADLOCKS,
LONGER-TERM UNCERTAINTY
 &HT;    With MIDEAST-CLINTON and MIDEAST-SECURITY
 &HT;    EDS: This is information suitable for a box or graphic and could
be run with a file map showing Jewish settlements and the latest
Palestinian -controlled territories.
 &HT;    By LARRY KAPLOW
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service (at)
<TEXT>
<P>
   JERUSALEM _ President Clinton's visit to Israel and
Palestinian-controlled areas, which begins this weekend, was
originally intended to cement the agreement he mediated in October
at the Wye River Plantation in Maryland. Now it looks like Clinton
will have to push, yet again, for the Israelis and Palestinians to
keep the peace process moving.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON'S JOB ON HIS MIDEAST TRIP:
</P>
<P>
   _ Witness the Palestine Liberation Organization reaffirm that
the group's charter no longer calls for the destruction of Israel a
move demanded by Israel.
</P>
<P>
   _ Convince Israeli leader Benjamin Netanyahu to restart the
phased Israeli troop withdrawals from the West Bank. The next is
due on Dec. 18.
</P>
<P>
   _ Convince Arafat to quell anti-Israeli riots by Palestinians
that have occurred almost daily for more than a week.
</P>
<P>
   _ Settle a post-Wye argument between the two sides about the
kinds of prisoners Israel is supposed to release from jail.
</P>
<P>
   IN COMING MONTHS, PALESTINIANS AND ISRAELIS ARE TO NEGOTIATE:
</P>
<P>
   _ Whether Israel will share Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
   _ What kind of self-rule or statehood the Palestinians will
ultimately have.
</P>
<P>
   _ The final borders between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
   _ Whether 3.4 million Palestinian refugees will be allowed to
return to land their families lost in Israel.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
