   A. BLUEPRINTS FOR PEOPLE - BUT HOW TO READ THEM? A look at human
embryonic stem cells, the cells that caused a furore when
scientists said they could culture and grow them in the laboratory,
with all sorts of interesting potential uses. By Nicholas Wade.
1,600 words + graphic.
</P>
<P>
   B. DENTISTS WIELD LASERS AGAINST DECAY A combination of new
technology and new treatments - laser beams that work on the hard
enamel of teeth and computerized x-rays - are promising patients
freedom from drilling, anaesthesia and pain. The treatments appear,
in their initial stages, to be safer, more accurate and faster than
traditional methods. By Holcomb B. Noble. 1,300 words + photo.
</P>
