   NYTBOOK-WONDER-NYTSF, SURPASSING WONDER, The Invention of the
Bible and the Talmuds, By Donald Harman Akenson. 658 pp. New York:
Harcourt Brace &AMP; Company. $35. A new study of the origins of
Scripture and how it has changed.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-GIBRAN-1000&AMP;ADD-NYTSF, PROPHET, The Life and Times of
Kahlil Gibran, By Robin Waterfield. Illustrated. 366 pp. New York:
St. Martin's Press. $25.95. KAHLIL GIBRAN, Man and Poet: A New
Biography, By Suheil Bushrui and Joe Jenkins. Illustrated. 372 pp.
Boston: Oneworld Pubs. $28.95. Two new biographies of Kahlil
Gibran, the Lebanese poet and philosopher.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-TROLLOPE-NYTSF, FANNY TROLLOPE, The Life and Adventures
of a Clever Woman. By Pamela Neville-Sington. Illustrated. 416 pp.
New York: Viking. $29.95. ``A vulgar pushing woman'': that was
Robert Browning's description of the fearless Fanny Trollope.
</P>
<P>
   NYTBOOK-DANDY-NYTSF, THE COWBOY AND THE DANDY, Crossing Over
From Romanticism to Rock and Roll. By Perry Meisel. Illustrated.
156 pp. New York: Oxford Press. $24.95. According to Perry Meisel,
the English Romantics paved the way for rock-and-roll.
