<P>
   AETNA-PRUDENTIAL (Undated) _ Aetna acquires Prudential
Healthcare for $1 billion in cash and debt issuance, expanding its
health benefit membership in nine states by about 6.6 million
people. Aetna will also more than double its dental coverage to
more than 15 million people. The transaction gets Prudential out of
the increasingly competitive managed-care industry, while giving
Aetna, which earlier this year bought New York Life's healthcare
business for $1.05 billion, increased leverage to negotiate prices
with providers. By Milt Freudenheim.
</P>
<P>
   With graphc.
</P>
<P>
   ERICSSON-OUTLOOK (Rome) _ Ericsson of Sweden says that profit
and sales will not meet expectations this year because of weak
demand for public phone networks and mobile phones and that it will
announce the layoff of as many as 10,000 people next month. Its
stock falls as much as 19 percent in Stockholm, and its depository
receipts follow suit in this country. By John Tagliabue.
</P>
<P>
   MCI-CUTBACK (New York) _ Folo on reports that MCI Worldcom is
moving to cut billions of dollars in expenses by undertaking a
sweeping cost-cutting program that is expected to include as many
as 3,750 layoffs. By Seth Schiesel.
</P>
<P>
   NATSEMI-EARNINGS (Undated) _ National Semiconductor will post
earnings and is expected to come in with a loss of 50 cents a
share. By Lawrence M. Fisher.
</P>
