with 44 states, agreeing to pay $2.4 million in cash and donate
$3.6 million in toys to Toys for Tots. By Dana Canedy.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-ANTITRUST (Washington) _ Testimony and other daily
doings at the Microsoft antiturst trial. By Steve Lohr.
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN-RATES (London) _ The Bank of England cuts its benchmark
lending rate one-half point, to 6.25 percent, the third consecutive
monthly reduction, in an effort to avert a deeper economic slowdown
and to narrow the gap with the 3 percent rate among the euro
nations. By Warren Hoge.
</P>
<P>
   VENEZUELA-COLA (Undated) _ Coca-Cola and Pepsico are fighting it
out for the hearts and minds of Venezuela's 22 million people. By
Constance L. Hays.
</P>
<P>
   MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ The daily Marketplace column.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ At 1:50 p.m., the industrial average was
down 94 points. Elsewhere, prices decreased 0.8 percent in Tokyo
and 0.4 percent in Hong Kong. They fell 0.6 percent in Frankfurt,
0.1 percent in London, and 0.4 percent in Mexico. They were flat in
Brazil. On the American debt market, the long bond was up 19/32
point at midday, with the yield at 4.95 percent. By Robert D.
Hershey Jr.
</P>
