   PRIUS-AUTO-AZR (Phoenix) _ The little Toyota Prius hardly seemed
worth a second glance, parked at the curb with a dozen sleek and
exotic examples of electric cars and trucks. But ordinary as it may
appear, there's a critical difference between Prius and the other
electric vehicles being demonstrated Wednesday in downtown Phoenix.
This is the world's first mass-produced car with hybrid power _
part gasoline engine and part electric motor _ providing the
benefits of low emissions and high gas mileage in a real-world
vehicle that can be driven anywhere. By Bob Golfen.
