<P>
   TEXAS FORTS-TRAIL-TEX (Menard, Texas) _ Thirty years ago, the
Texas Historical Commission officially designated a 650-mile route
through the west central part of the state as a historical path to
be known as the Texas Forts Trail. The trail includes a Spanish
presidio, eight frontier forts of both the ruined and restored
variety from the 19th century, and highlights of the communities
that have sprung up around them. It commemorates the legacy of
cavalrymen and pioneers who drew a line in the dust and offered to
fight anyone who made the mistake of trying to remove them. By Jeff
Guinn.
</P>
<P>
