By Alessandra Stanley.
</P>
<P>
   BELLAGIO-TRAVEL-AZR (Las Vegas) - Bellagio, the most expensive
hotel ever built (for now), stands on the western edge of an
8.5-acre artificial lake. At regular intervals throughout each
evening, lyrical sprinklers animate the water. Framed through the
falling mist and the twinkle lights decorating the lakeside
foliage, Bellagio appears every bit as enchanting, romantic,
stately and dignified as its TV commercials promise. By Dave
Walker.
</P>
<P>
   JERSEY CITY-TRAVEL-AZR (Jersey City, N.J.) - Although travel
writers tend to wax eloquent about the big tourist destinations and
travel sections in the nation's newspapers tend to cover mainstream
events with ``what-to-see'' stories emphasizing places with giant
smiling mice or beachfront hotels, a great deal of our travel is in
between the places we actually want to be. Thus, I came to New
Jersey, to find cheap lodging for the nights while spending the
days in Manhattan. But travelers learn that sometimes there are
treats where you least expect them, that come unbidden to you while
you wait for something else. By Richard Nilsen.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-MACAO (Undated) _ Gang war casts pall on handover of
Macao. By Mark Landler.
