<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE BUSINESS BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These business stories for release Friday, December 11, 1998,
are moving today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   Stories are moving in the financial (f) category. Stories also
moving in lifestyle will be marked with (f, l).
</P>
<P>
   Separate budgets move daily with spot news, features, sports and
commentary.
</P>
<P>
   All stories have moved, except those with an ETA.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   AETNA _ ATLANTA _ Aetna Inc., the biggest U.S. health insurer,
agreed to acquire Prudential HealthCare for $500 million in cash
and $500 million in debt, expanding its business in nine states.
The agreement adds 6.6 million people covered by Prudential,
boosting Aetna's health-benefit coverage to about 22.4 million and
making it the largest U.S. managed-care company. Aetna will also
become the largest provider of dental benefits, more than doubling
its dental coverage to more than 15 million people. (Miller,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AUS-AETNA-BUYS-PRUDENTIAL _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Aetna Inc. is buying
the healthcare business of Prudential Insurance Co. of America for
$1 billion in a deal that Aetna said will make it the nation's
biggest health benefit provider. It also would be the biggest
health insurer in Texas and in Central Texas, after Aetna's
previously announced purchase of NYLcare. Because both Aetna and
Prudential are already big in this area, the deal could face its
biggest hurdles from regulators in Texas. (Park, Austin
American-Satesman)
</P>
<P>
   CARSON _ ATLANTA _ Pursuing tip that billionaire investor George
Soros' fund is lending money to help Savannah-based hair care
products company Carson to help the financially-strapped company.
Carson also is selling part of its Cutex business to a San
Francisco-based investment firm for $30 million. (Poole, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   TESTDRIVE-MUSTANG _ Review of all new 1999 Ford Mustang, which
is getting rave reviews all over the country. Note: Atlanta is one
of two cities under consideration for the Mustang Museum. (DeVault,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
