   AETNA _ ATLANTA _ Aetna Inc., the biggest U.S. health insurer,
agreed to acquire Prudential HealthCare for $500 million in cash
and $500 million in debt, expanding its business in nine states.
The agreement adds 6.6 million people covered by Prudential,
boosting Aetna's health-benefit coverage to about 22.4 million and
making it the largest U.S. managed-care company. Aetna wi
</P>
