<P>
   FBC-AA-BACKS _ Two of the best running backs in the nation will
meet Saturday in the Division I-AA semifinals as Aaron Stecker of
Western Illinois faces Adrian Peterson of Georgia Southern. Stecker
rushed for 26 touchdowns and was a consensus All-American last
season and has rushed for more than 1,400 yards this season, but
his accomplishments pale in comparison to Peterson's 2,342 yards
and 33 touchdowns. Both teams have defenses that have struggled
this season, so the game could develop into a showdown of the
talented running backs. (Reese) 20''
</P>
<P>
   FBC-KELSO-COLUMN_AUSTIN _ Six years ago, Jackie Sherrill had a
bull castrated on a practice field in front of his Mississippi
State players to get them fired up for the team's season opener
against Texas. So, with the same teams playing in the Cotton Bowl
on New Year's Day, you're wondering what surprise moves he has up
his sleeve. (Kelso, Austin American-Statesman). MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGE BASKETBALL
</P>
<P>
   BKC-JASONCOLLIER _ After transferring from Indiana University,
Jason Collier has been anxiously waiting to begin his career at
Georgia Tech. Sunday, the moment will arrive. Collier, an honorable
mention all-Big 10 selection as a freshman at Indiana in 1997, is
expected to make a huge impact for the Jackets and his arrival
couldn't come at a better time for a team that has been riddled
with injuries. Also, he arrives in time to face rival Georgia.
(Arey, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
