<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    FOR WATER, FOOD AND DEMOCRACY, U.S. AIDS PALESTINIANS
 &HT;    EDS: Material for A box/graphic to accompany
MIDEAST-DEVELOPMENT.
 &HT;    Advance for release Sunday, Dec. 13, but may be used prior to
that.
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service(at)
<TEXT>
<P>
   Since the 1994, the United States Agency for International
Development has provided assistance in the Gaza Strip and the West
Bank worth $75 million a year. Projects have included:
</P>
<P>
   _ A major water pipeline, using one of the few Palestinian water
sources, to improve service to the towns of Bethlehem and Hebron.
</P>
<P>
   _ Repairs to about 20 miles of sewer systems in Gaza City,
reducing street flooding for 200,000 people.
</P>
<P>
   _ Training for 2,800 business managers and 10,000 loans from
small businesses.
</P>
<P>
   _ Marketing support for food producers.
</P>
<P>
   _ Supervision of the 1996 presidential and parliamentary
elections by 1,500 monitors.
</P>
<P>
   _ Training and furnishings for the Palestinian Legislative
Council.
</P>
<P>
   - By Larry Kaplow
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
