<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Friday, Dec. 11, and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact Tom Hicks at the Daily News, (818)
713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   AETNA-PRUDENTIAL (Los Angeles) _ After more than a year of
speculation, Aetna, the nation's largest health insurance carrier,
announced Thursday that it will purchase Prudential Healthcare for
$1 billion in cash and debt. By Ben Sullivan. (Will move in the
``f'' financial, ``n'' California and the ``a'' national news
files.)
</P>
<P>
   SEAGRAM-MUSIC (Los Angeles) _ Seagram Co. confirmed Thursday
that it will significantly reduce employment at its music
operations by what's widely believed to be about 3,000 jobs over
the next six months. By Dave McNary.
</P>
<P>
   COYOTE-SHARES (Los Angeles) _ A day after its shares fell 45
percent because of a critical article on a financial Web site,
Westlake Village, Calif.-based Coyote Network Systems Inc. said
Thursday the article was littered with errors and asked for a
retraction. By Deborah Adamson.
</P>
