   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Friday, Dec. 11. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
WOLVES (Undated) - Analysis of who's slaughtering the wolves
released in Arizona and the cultural tensions surfacing in the
mystery. By STEVE YOZWIAK. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
WAKINGNED-MOVIE (Undated) - ``Waking Ned Devine'' is a sly comic
delight about two schemers contriving to snag an undeserved share
of the winnings of the Irish lottery. Filled with sarcastic Irish
wit and sardonic humor, this charmer is as funny and delightful as
``The Englishman Who Went Up the Hill But Came Down the Mountain''
or ``The Secret of Roan Inish.'' 4 stars. By BOB FENSTER. Story
will move in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
BANNEN-MOVIE (Mesa, Ariz.) - In ``Waking Ned Divine,'' Ian Bannen
is the perfect Irishman. When you meet him, he appears to be the
quintessential British actor. So what's he doing living in Mesa,
Ariz.? Bannen fell in love with the Arizona desert when acting in
his first American movie, ``Flight of the Phoenix,'' which was shot
out of Yuma in 1966. Bannen's lastest film, ``Waking Ned Divine''
is a winsome comedy about two old Irish men who scheme to get a
share of big lottery winnings in their small village. By BOB
FENSTER. Story moved in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
STARTREK-MOVIE (Undated) - No. 9 in the series has Capt. Picard
(Patrick Stewart) and his crew violating Federation orders to
rescue the inhabitants of a technology-rejecting planet. The story
is barely substantial enough, the pace sluggish and the special
effects tinny. While this Trekker-pleasing, jargon-intensive movie
should satisfy the cult, it may leave outsiders wondering: Are they
actually speaking English? 2 stars. By BOB FENSTER. Story will move
in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
STARTREK-BOOK (Phoenix) - An interview with a guy who's written a
really good book about ``Star Trek,'' timed to coincide with
release of new ``Star Trek'' movie. By DAVE WALKER. Story will move
in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
