of the Red Sea in ``The 10 Commandments'' and ``Prince of Egypt.''
How'd they do it, then and now. By DON RENFROE. Story will move in
the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SIMPLEPLAN-MOVIE (Undated) - Three guys stumble upon a bag
containing nearly $5 million in this thriller about how ordinary
people crack under the pressure of trying to get away with an
ever-widening web of crime. The movie is as flawed as their plan,
primarily because the characters never develop into people we
either like or hate enough to care about what happens to them. 2
stars. By BOB FENSTER. Story moved in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
AUTO COLUMN (Undated) - Is this the greatest toy ever invented or
what? It's like one of my kids' Hot Wheels came to life, and I got
to drive it around. Everything you want to know about the Plymouth
Prowler can be summed up in three letters: F-U-N. This wedgy
eggplant doesn't have a serious bone in its chassis. Nor should it.
By BOB GOLFEN. Story moved in the ``L'' category. EMBARGOED FOR
SATURDAY, DEC. 12. &QL; 
