<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR FRIDAY, DECEMBER 11
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Friday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-TEXAS-EXECUTE-NYT (moved on Monday, Dec. 7)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Dec. 7,
about Joseph Stanley Faulder, a Canadian who is on death row in
Texas and whose case has drawn attention from the Canadian
Government and Secretary of State Madeleine K. Albright, misstated
the outcome of a case against Rubin (Hurricane) Carter, an American
boxer who spent 19 years in prison and is supporting Mr. Faulder's
efforts to avoid execution. Mr. Carter was not acquitted of murder;
his conviction was overturned twice, and prosecutors declined to
try him a third time.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SCI-MALTHUS-POPULATION-NYT (moved on Monday, Dec. 7)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Dec. 7,
about a meeting of anthropologists misstated part of the group's
name. It is the American Anthropological Association, not Society.
The article also misspelled the surname of a participant from
Pennsylvania State University. He is Dr. Kenneth Weiss, not Wise.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-GIFTS-ONLINE-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Dec. 9)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Dec. 9,
about holiday-related Web sites misstated two addresses. E-Mail
Santa is www.emailsanta.com.
</P>
<P>
   American Greetings cards is www.americangreetings.com/index.pd.
</P>
<P>
   BC-PATENTS-NYT (moved on Sunday, Dec. 6)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Dec. 6,
about a technology that lets on-line companies pay commissions for
customer referrals from other Web sites misidentified the owner of
Travelocity, a site that uses it. The owner is AMR, not Microsoft.
</P>
