A4027 &Cx1f; tad-z
u w &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-IMPBOX11-COX     12-10 0163
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-IMPBOX11-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    What's next in impeachment process
 &HT;    By Staff reports
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _
</P>
<P>
   Today _ House Judiciary Committee continues debate on four
articles of impeachment; voting could begin on some of the
articles.
</P>
<P>
   Dec. 12 _ Final committee vote on impeachment articles expected.
</P>
<P>
   Dec. 17 _ If at least one article of impeachment is approved by
the Judiciary Committee, the full House begins debate.
</P>
<P>
   Dec. 18 _ Final House votes expected.
</P>
<P>
   Jan. 6 _ If the House passes at least one article of
impeachment, a trial begins in the Senate sometime after the 106th
Congress begins on this date. Senate Majority Leader Trent Lott has
not yet set a schedule for a trial and there is no indication how
long a trial would last.
</P>
<P>
   Jan. 19 _ The president is scheduled to deliver the State of the
Union address to a joint session of Congress.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
