<P>
   (NYT43) CAMBRIDGE, England -- Dec. 10, 1998 -- WORM-GENE, 12-10
-- In a landmark achievement, researchers have deciphered the
genetic program of a microscopic roundworm known as Caenorhabditis
elegans and used in laboratories throughout the world as a means to
explore biology at the genetic level. John Sulston is one of the
scientists who deciphered the genome. (Jonathan Player/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT42) LOS ANGELES -- Dec. 10, 1998 -- IMPEACH-MOOD-2, 12-10 --
At the Fashion Square mall in Sherman Oaks, the solemn business of
impeachment seems even farther away than three time zones and 3,000
miles. ``The guy's a dog, but what he does is up to Hillary,'' says
Alicia Verde, shopping in Sherman Oaks with her two-year old
daughter, Rory. ``He'll have his karma.'' (Monica Almeida/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT41) LOS ANGELES -- Dec. 10, 1998 -- IMPEACH-MOOD-1, 12-10 --
At the Fashion Square mall in Sherman Oaks, the prospect that the
House of Representatives may vote to approve articles of
impeachment seems only another irritant to a public seemingly
powerless to change the procession of events. ``It troubles me to
see them behaving in this irresponsible manner,'' says Kermit
Eller, 68, a retired engineer and a Republican, of his party's
tactics. (Monica Almeida/New York Times Photo)
