<P>
   (NYT38) COLUMBUS, Miss. -- Dec. 10, 1998 -- MISS-MURDERS, 12-10
-- A Neighborhood Watch sign stands outside a home in downtown
Columbus. The separate murders of three elderly people over a seven
week period have the inhabitants of this drowsy Mississippi city on
edge; many senior citizens are choosing to stay close to home. (Joe
Oliveira/Tuscaloosa News) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT37) BOYNTON BEACH, Fla. -- Dec. 10, 1998 -- DOLL-LADY-COX,
12-10 -- ``I just started buying them because they were cute, and
it was so easy to do,'' says Eva Becker, surrounded by just a small
part of her doll collection. She still doesn't think like a
collector. No selling, no trading and, most definitely, no
scrounging around flea markets. Mrs. Becker just calls up the
shop-at-home shows and waits for more to arrive. (David
Spencer/Palm Beach Post Photo)
