<P>
   (NYT14) LONDON -- Dec. 10, 1998 -- ADV. FOR MON., DEC. 14 --
EUROPE-SUCCESS-HNS, 12-09 -- Andrew Ramroop, a black immigrant from
the Caribbean island of Trinidad, does a final fitting for an
Italian client at Maurice Sedwell, the Savile Row establishment
which he owns and runs. ``Yes, there is an element of surprise when
customers come in off the street and are welcomed by a West
Indian,'' says Ramroop. Many see his success as a sign that the
immigrant story in Europe is not all exclusion and failure. (Kerwin
Plevka/Houston Chronicle Photo)
</P>
<P>
